                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Williams</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-07-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 23, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>From independent sources, apparently authentic, Department is advised that Habana
                    volunteers parade 24th instant and may demand <pb facs="0864" n="770"
                        xml:id="pg_770"/> instant execution of Sanguily and Aguirre and probably
                    other Americans. American citizens under treaty provisions are admittedly
                    entitled to trial by ordinary civil procedure. Department is convinced that
                    authorities will never yield to a demand for summary proceedings but ask that
                    precautions will be taken to prevent extrajudicial violence. The gravity of the
                    situation which would result should any injury be done them can not be
                    overestimated. Communicate this to the proper authorities.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
